          <h2 class="featurette-heading">Mongolia<br><span class="text-muted">Horses and nomads and shit.</span></h2>
          <p class="lead">
          Mongolia is home to the last horse-based nomadic culture in the world, where almost half of the population lives a traditional nomadic lifestyle. The vast stretch of prairies, pristine rivers, and lakes that are the key to nomadic existence also hold immense amounts of natural deposits such as gold, copper, coal, uranium, and other industrial minerals. Naturally, the country has a booming mining sector that is aggressively exploring precious metals. In the last two years alone, the government granted 3000 exploration permits. In addition, the number of artisanal miners grew exponentially as mining became a secondary source of income for most families. The rampant explosion of outdated mining practices has caused river and groundwater systems to be polluted with the invisible but toxic heavy metals and mining waste products.
          </p>
        </div>
