        <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-7">
          <p class="lead">
          The OASIS-Mongolia project aims to solve this problem by empowering nomadic communities by providing a low cost, community based testing system for lead, mercury, cyanide, uranium, and arsenic in drinking water. Leveraging existing cellphone networks in Mongolia, nomads can send data and receive results on their cellphones along with information regarding nearby clean water sources. Furthermore, we plan to make the project OASIS a self-sustaining environmental monitoring tool that not only measures water quality but a tool that provides an economic incentive to data collectors (nomads) and an affordable national level water quality monitoring system.
          </p>
        </div>
